=================
SmartConfigParser
=================

SmartConfigParser add missing default value in ConfigParser module.

    #!/usr/bin/env python

    from smartconfigparser import Config

    config = Config()
    config.read('config.ini')

    user = config.get('SECTION', 'user', 'default user value')
    month_per_year = config.getint('SECTION', 'int', 12)
    hour_price = config.getfloat('SECTION', 'float', 125.12)
    debug = config.getboolean('SECTION', 'boolean', True)

    # if SECTION does not exist in config.ini use default value
    print(user, month_per_year, hour_price, debug)


Installation
============

Install it with pip:

    pip install smartconfigparser


